Step 6 - Flow

1.  User selects an SMD line.
2.  JavaScript sends an AJAX request to autofill.php.
3.  autofill.php gets the printer folder from machines.php.
4.  PHP finds the latest TXT log file.
5.  PHP reads the log.
6.  Required parameters are extracted.
7.  Data is returned as JSON.
8.  Form fields are updated automatically.
9.  The page does not reload.

Production Recommendation

Instead of storing printer IPs in machines.php, store them in a MySQL
table (printer_ips). When a printer IP changes, update only the database
instead of editing PHP code.
